h3. Issue Summary

When clicking a Jira Menu Header link (EG Dashboards, Projects, etc), a blue border is displayed. This can contrast in a disturbing way when Jira's default theme is customized via the "Look and Feel" feature.

(i) Unable to reproduce in 7.13.16

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Browse to Jira Admin -> System -> Look and Feel, then upload this *logo image* to customize the theme: [^ceilingcat.png]. You will note that the theme is customised to a brown color. 
 # Now, click "Projects" menu bar item

h3. Expected Results

The border colour should follow the theme settings, thus be visually pleasing. It should probably follow the "{*}Header navigation - highlight background colour{*}"

!image-2021-11-22-15-59-25-722.png!
h3. Actual Results

The border is shown in a non-customisable blue

!image-2021-11-22-15-56-08-234.png!

The CSS is
{code:java}
.aui-header .aui-header-logo>a:focus, .aui-header .aui-header-primary>.aui-nav>li>a:not(.aui-button):focus, .aui-header .aui-header-secondary>.aui-nav>li>a:not(.aui-button):focus: {
 box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 2px var(--aui-focus);
}{code}
Which is in-turn set to
{code:java}
--aui-focus: #4c9aff;{code}
h3. Workaround

Add the following code block to the [Announcement Banner. |https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver/configuring-an-announcement-banner-938846985.html]You can customize the #000 value to whatever HTML HEX color code you prefer
{code:java}
<!-- Workaround for JRASERVER-73031 -->
<style>
.aui-header .aui-header-logo>a:focus, .aui-header .aui-header-primary>.aui-nav>li>a:not(.aui-button):focus, .aui-header .aui-header-secondary>.aui-nav>li>a:not(.aui-button):focus {box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 2px #000}
</style>
{code}

As of Jira 8.20, the API's for screens have changed.

We have a script listed on our [Advanced cleanup|https://confluence.atlassian.com/clean/advanced-cleanup-1018789335.html] guide that no longer works to delete unused screens.

In [8.13.11|https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/8.13.11/], the Screens API looks like this:
{code}
public ViewFieldScreens(FieldScreenManager fieldScreenManager,
FieldScreenFactory fieldScreenFactory,
FieldScreenSchemeManager fieldScreenSchemeManager,
WorkflowManager workflowManager)
{code}

As of [8.20|https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/8.20.0/], the API now looks like this:
{code}
public ViewFieldScreens(FieldScreenManager fieldScreenManager,
FieldScreenFactory fieldScreenFactory,
FieldScreenSchemeManager fieldScreenSchemeManager,
FieldScreenService fieldScreenService,
WorkflowManager workflowManager,
JiraAuthenticationContext jiraAuthenticationContext,
com.atlassian.webresource.api.assembler.PageBuilderService pageBuilderService)
{code}

Because of this change, the script now gives a "cannot find matching method" because of the change. The scripts on this page should be modified to account for this change in API.

h3. Issue Summary
When workflow condition verification is set to be skipped, negated condition within the workflow caused the *passesCondition()* method to (incorrectly) return false and fail the flow.

When there's negated condition is in place, the request goes into this problematic *If* clause: 
{code:title=com.opensymphony.workflow.AbstractWorkflow.java}
protected boolean passesCondition(ConditionDescriptor conditionDesc, Map transientVars, PropertySet ps, int currentStepId)
...
try {
    boolean passed = condition.passesCondition(transientVars, args, ps); 

                    if (conditionDesc.isNegate()) {
                        passed = !passed;
                    }...
{code}
The *boolean passed = condition.passesCondition()* should always return *true* when we skip workflow condition verification but the *If* clause inverted the result causing it to always return *false* when there's negated condition in place.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
N/A

h3. Expected Results
When condition verification is set to be skipped, the method should return 'true' regardless if condition is negated or not.

h3. Actual Results
When condition verification is set to be skipped, the method returns 'false' when there is a negated condition in place.

h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Problem Definition
Currently Jira Data Center support.zip, brings some node's information (healthcheck, localq, name and address), but these information are not clear if a node is available and replicating or not, being necessary to run some SQL queries to get this information and share on support tickets.

h3. Suggested Solution
Bring the results of the below SQL queries on the Support.zip:
{code:xml}
SELECT max(id), node_id FROM replicatedindexoperation GROUP BY node_id;
SELECT * FROM nodeindexcounter;
SELECT * FROM clusternode;
SELECT * FROM clusternodeheartbeat;
{code}
 
h3. Workaround 
Run the below SQL queries and send trhough the ticket:
{code:xml}
SELECT max(id), node_id FROM replicatedindexoperation GROUP BY node_id;
SELECT * FROM nodeindexcounter;
SELECT * FROM clusternode;
SELECT * FROM clusternodeheartbeat;
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

Third-party apps/plugins are being loaded even when they are not being used in the projects. 
This increases the load time for projects that do not need or even use the app/plugin.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Install Jira Server/Data Center;
 # Install 3rd party app/plugin (IE. XRay);
 # Create a new empty project with no customization;
 # Create a new issue with no customization;
 # Open the browser Developer tools;
 # Change to the Network tab;
 # Load the newly created issue on step 4;

h3. Expected Results

It is expected that third-party apps do not load on projects that are not using it.
h3. Actual Results

The browser Developer Tools shows a lot of JavaScript files from third-party apps being loaded even if they are not used in a project.
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
